  "texts": [
    "• The Data Act [58], proposed in 2022 and entered into force on 11 January 2023, establishes harmonized rules on data access and use (1.)",
    "between businesses; (2.)",
    "between businesses and consumers; (3.)",
    "and between businesses and the public sector.",
    "The new measures complement the DGA, yet the former regulates processes and structures that facilitate voluntary data sharing, while the Data Act clarifies rights and usage conditions regarding data, sustaining incentives for data holders to continue investing in high-quality data generation."
